02467 class glFont
02468 {
02469 public:
02470   glFont();
02471   ~glFont();
02475   int  read(const char *filename);
02479   int  lineHeight();
02483   int  charWidth(unsigned char c);
02487   int  stringWidth(const char *str);
02492   void drawString(float x, float y, const char *str);
02496   void setZoom(float factor);
02500   void setRotation(int angle);
02504   void setFontSize(int pitch, float factor);
02505 
02506 private:
02507   // Information about a glyph. Tex_y2 can be calculated from tex_y1
02508   // and _tex_line_height (see below). Advance is the width of the
02509   // glyph in screen space.
02510   struct Glyph
02511   {
02512     float tex_x1, tex_y1, tex_x2;
02513     int advance;
02514   };
02515   // An array to store the glyphs.
02516   //Glyph* _glyphs;
02517   Glyph  _glyphs[256];
02518   // A table to quickly get the glyph belonging to a character.
02519   Glyph* _table[256];
02520   // The line height, in screen space and in texture space, and the
02521   // OpenGL id of the font texture.
02522   GLuint _line_height, _texture;
02523   float _tex_line_height;
02524   double zoom,zoom0;
02525   int    angle_128x128;
02526 };
